## Overview

The vault search bar lets you find any data inside your vault without manually navigating through tabs or scrolling through tables. It is available from the top navigation header whenever you are inside a vault, and opens a full search window where you can search across records, tables, schema fields, connections, and assistants in one place. Search is available to all vault members — **ADMIN**, **BUILDER**, **CONTRIBUTOR**, and **VIEWER** — and can only be accessed from within a vault.

---

## When to Search Your Vault

Use vault search when you need to:

- Quickly locate a specific patient record, case, or entry by name, ID, or any field value
- Find a table by name without scrolling through the sidebar
- Look up a schema field definition to check its type, description, or whether it is required
- Navigate directly to a connection without going through the Connections tab

